**Authors**: Kenneth Tsz Hin Ng, Jane Doe  
**Journal**: *Journal of Actuarial Science*  
**Published**: November 2024  
**DOI**: [10.1234/example-doi](https://doi.org/10.1234/example-doi)  

### Abstract
This study introduces a novel stochastic model for catastrophic risk assessment in the insurance industry. It leverages advanced statistical techniques to improve predictive accuracy for rare and extreme events, incorporating new perspectives on dependence structures and tail risk.

### Keywords
Stochastic modeling, catastrophic risk, insurance, actuarial science

